cerentGenericNodeTime.name: cerentGenericNodeTime
cerentGenericNodeTime.description: Indicates current local time as reflected by the Cisco OTBU equipment. The format this scalar is YYYYMMDDhhmmss{S/D}. E.g., 20011103133453D means 1:34:53 PM PDT on 03/Nov/2001 19990614095436S means 9:54:36 AM PST on 14/Jun/1999. If the last octet is S then the time is standard time. Otherwise it is D to indicate it is daylight saving time, if applicable

cerentGenericAlarmCount.name: cerentGenericAlarmCount
cerentGenericAlarmCount.description: Total number of active alarms in the Cisco ONS network element, ONS 15327, 15310. This equals the total number of rows in cerentGenericAlarmTable at any time.

cerentGenericAlarmTable.name: cerentGenericAlarmTable
cerentGenericAlarmTable.description: This table has all currently raised conditions for the network node. A Condition is a fault or status detected by hardware or software.

cerentGenericAlarmIndex.name: cerentGenericAlarmIndex
cerentGenericAlarmIndex.description: Uniquely identifies each entry in alarm table. May not start with one and there may be some missing numbers.

cerentGenericAlarmObjectType.name: cerentGenericAlarmObjectType
cerentGenericAlarmObjectType.description: This will indicate what is the type of the entity which raised this alarm. ( E.g., DS3, etherBridge, VT-TERM, etc ) The NMS is expected to use this value to decide which table to poll for further info about the alarm

cerentGenericAlarmSlotNumber.name: cerentGenericAlarmSlotNumber
cerentGenericAlarmSlotNumber.description: This will indicate what is the slot of the object which raised this alarm. If not relevant to the alarm, will be zero.

cerentGenericAlarmPortNumber.name: cerentGenericAlarmPortNumber

cerentGenericAlarmLineNumber.name: cerentGenericAlarmLineNumber
cerentGenericAlarmLineNumber.description: This will indicate what is the port of the object which raised this alarm. If not relevant to the alarm, will be zero.

cerentGenericAlarmObjectIndex.name: cerentGenericAlarmObjectIndex
cerentGenericAlarmObjectIndex.description: Every alarm is raised by an object and this object is an entry in a specific table. This is the index of the object in that table E.g., if the alarm is interface related, this index is the index of the interface in the interface table.

cerentGenericAlarmType.name: cerentGenericAlarmType
cerentGenericAlarmType.description: Indicates what the exact nature of the alarm. See the CerentGenericAlarmType TC for mapping details

cerentGenericAlarmState.name: cerentGenericAlarmState
cerentGenericAlarmState.description: Specifies alarm severity and service affecting status ( SA/NSA ). Only {minor|major|critical}+{NA|NSA} alarms and standing conditions will be represented here. However, this mib object is included in each trap dispatched and in the trap this object can contain all the possible values of CerentNotificationClass type.

cerentGenericAlarmTimeStamp.name: cerentGenericAlarmTimeStamp
cerentGenericAlarmTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime when this entry was created. This is accurate only upto a second.

cerentGenericAlarmObjectName.name: cerentGenericAlarmObjectName
cerentGenericAlarmObjectName.description: TL1-style user-visible name which uniquely identifies an object in the system

cerentGenericAlarmAdditionalInfo.name: cerentGenericAlarmAdditionalInfo
cerentGenericAlarmAdditionalInfo.description: Additional information for the alarm object. In the current version of the MIB, this object contains the following information :- a) Provisioned description for alarms of type 'failureDetectedExternalToTheNE'. This object would be a null string if no additional information is specified.

cerentGenericAlarmStatus.name: cerentGenericAlarmStatus
cerentGenericAlarmStatus.description: Represents if an alarm is currently raised or cleared.

cerentGenericAlarmServiceAffecting.name: cerentGenericAlarmServiceAffecting
cerentGenericAlarmServiceAffecting.description: Specifies whether the alarm that is being sent out is Service Affecting (SA) or Non- Service Affecting (NSA).

cerentGenericReportedAlarmCount.name: cerentGenericReportedAlarmCount
cerentGenericReportedAlarmCount.description: Number of alarms currently reported against Cisco ONS platform. This equals the number of rows in cerentGenericReportedAlarmTable.

cerentGenericReportedAlarmTable.name: cerentGenericReportedAlarmTable
cerentGenericReportedAlarmTable.description: This table has the list of alarms currently reported for the Cisco ONS node. It does not include any cleared alarms. The alarms in this table are in compliance with Telcordia GR-253. This means that if a network problem causes two alarms, such a as loss of frame(LOF) and loss of signal(LOS), only LOS alarm will be in this table because it supersedes and replaces the LOF.
